content: This app should be used in a computer science course on "How to Make a Really Wonderful App Completely Unuseable.". I've recommended it dozens of times, but now, rather than create a filter to let campers choose between "Reservable Sites" and "Non-Reservable Sites," Kampnik shoves a linked Website into our faces from Recreation.gov that constantly says "Oops, something went wrong! Please bear with us. " when I click on a campsite for viewing. I've seen more "bears" in this app than camping.
replyContent: Hi Bryan, Could you email us the name of the campground where you're seeing this behavior so we have the chance of resolving the issue?

content: Does what it claims, so is quite useful.

Just got started on this app. At first, to test its mettle, I tried looking up camps I've been to (mostly remote undeveloped camps that I prefer) and so far its mixed results. I don't see any way to submit a newly "discovered" camp via this app, nor any instructions on how to do so. Also, some camps don't have much info or photos, and there's no way to load those up either for a visual. So far, a mediocre app. I'll be looking around for another option.
replyContent: Hi Steve, Thanks for giving Kampnik a try. The focus of the app is on public car accessible campgrounds, so the remote undeveloped sites you reference probably aren't well represented. You can submit new campgrounds via the send feedback option, and photos are something we're working to improve. Happy camping!

content: Road trip to Chicago from LA with my Camp-Inn teardrop trailer. 6wks + 7000mi & found plenty of "off the beaten path" places to park my a##. A most wonderful app, indispensable for a person who likes to get off the grid. A+++++++! No ads, no commercial KOA/private "rv resorts". PERFECT!!!
Great app - used it extensively on month long road trip. I don't understand the purpose of the "Discover" button, though. All it does is take me to the a location in WA state. What am I missing?
replyContent: Hi Robert, So happy to hear you are enjoying Kampnik! There was an issue in Discover view with the previous release, but that has been resolved in the current release. Now the map should remember where you left off the last time you used the app. Happy camping!

content: I am so excited to have this app. There is nothing worse than having to go back and forth between the websites of all different kinds of public campgrounds. This app solves that! Everything is in one place. I think it was brilliant to use Google interface and Google internet searches because those always have the most up to date info. This is the best three bucks I've spent this year!
replyContent: Hi Mark and Renee, So glad to hear you are enjoying Kampnik's features. Thank you for taking the time to let us know how we're doing. Happy camping!!

content: Fantastic information for road trips with my tent or camper.
Does a good job with the amount of campgrounds it finds
website says camping spots for under $15 every site I looked at says $35 to $40 you can find camping sites like that on Google without paying for an app. ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜¡
We've been using Kampnik for the past month in BC Canada and the Pacific Northwest. So far it's been great for finding and reserving campsites in state and national parks.
Wouldn't be able to camp efficiently without it!
one of the best for public camping information. kampnik is a real time saver!
current thorough and very helpful tool for finding campsites!
There are much better apps than this one. I got a refund.
replyContent: Hi Nancy, Sorry to hear the app isn't what you expected. If you could let us know what you'd like to see in the app, we sure would appreciate the feedback.

content: Does not allow you to search within a certain area around a location.
replyContent: Hi Sara, Actually you can search an area around a location. Tap the search bar, then enter a town name near where you'd like to find campgrounds. Once you select a town name, the map will center on that location and you can use the map or campground list to traverse all of the campgrounds in the area. Give it a try, contact us if you need help.

content: Great app. Pretty accurate info, with only a couple exceptions that I've noted so far!!
replyContent: Hi Laura, Glad to hear you are enjoying Kampnik, happy camping!

content:
I just downloaded this app and it has already helped me find a ton of 
campgrounds I never new existed. Also easy user interface. I am a former 
programmer, I can appreciate the work involved in creating this 
application. Thumbs up to the development team
replyContent: Hi Jim, Thanks so much for taking the time to provide a review of Kampnik. And yes, it has taken a lot of work to create the app and even more to continue to maintain it. But it's all worth it when there is a review like this. Happy camping!

content:
A pretty good collection of campgrounds. Used it all the time during my 
recent road trip.
replyContent: Thanks Vasyl, We're glad to hear Kampnik served your needs on your tip. Happy camping.

content:
I love this site. The best. It is a very nice site and I wish more people 
would Install it
replyContent: Hi Billy, Thank you for taking the time to leave a review of Kampnik, we're so happy to hear you are enjoying the app. Happy camping!

content:
Amazing for finding campgrounds along with all the information you might 
need about them including photos, phone numbers, reviews, weather, and 
more. Has been extremely helpful while traveling. I recommend it to 
everyone, it's a steal.
replyContent: Thank you, Darijan. We love to hear when someone enjoys the app as much as we do. Happy camping!

content:
It doesn't even give you the prices of the campgrounds, that's pretty 
important in my opinion. It's pointless to download if you'll be off the 
grid and won't have phone reception
replyContent: Hi anonymous, We hate to hear the app isn't what you expected. In our app description, we explain what is and is not available offline. If you have any questions about how to download Google Map areas please contact us.

content:
Not so many private campgrounds on this site. I have camped in four states 
in the past month and only two are listed. Tried to suggest a few and app 
won't allow me to send . Also tab for send feedback won't send( could be a 
Google phone issue?) Disappointed I spent money on this app. Will go back 
to Google search...
replyContent: Hi, We're sorry to hear the app isn't what you expected, but we state in the app description that our focus is on public campgrounds. We do include some private campgrounds but that isn't our focus. If you would like a refund please email us via the app or the Google Play app profile page.

content: Luv this app up it all the time A+++
replyContent: Hi, We love Kampnik too, happy camping!

content:
Kampnik is by far the best campsite locating app out there. I was pretty 
worried when it stopped working (Google play issue, not app) but Bill from 
Keezo helped me diagnose and repair the issues I was having in a very 
professional and thorough manner. 5 stars for the app and 5 stars for the 
company support fof a full 10/10. Thank you!
replyContent: Hi Fuzz Wolf, Thank you for taking the time to tell us how we're doing, and it makes us so happy to hear how much you like the app. Happy camping!

content: Radical
replyContent: Hi Sam, We think Kampnik is radical too, happy camping!

content: This is awesome. Thank you!
replyContent: Hi Sieber, We're glad to hear you like the app, thank you for taking the time to leave a review. Happy camping!

content: I was at first disappointed that the maps feature would not work without wifi connection.  When I enquired I was informed that if I downloaded the google maps are of interest for access offline the app would show the maps offline.  Was very pleased.
replyContent: Hi Roger, We're happy to hear you're enjoying Kampnik. Small clarification: Kampnik does not require a wifi connection, maps are available on both cellular and wifi networks. For offline, you'll need to download a map area via Google Maps. Happy camping!

content: Has helped me find local, state and federal campgrounds in less traveled places.
replyContent: It's awesome to hear Kampnik is helping you find great places, happy trails!

content: Can't wait to use more in the coming years
replyContent: This is great to hear Merle, have fun!

content: I prefer public campgrounds to private ones. This app is very through in listing City, County, State and Federal Campgrounds. After selecting a particular campground it has info and links to the site.
replyContent: Hi Rick, Public campgrounds are our focus, we prefer them too. Thanks for giving Kampnik a try, we're so glad to hear it is helping you find great places to camp. Happy camping!

content: Accurate, fast, makes it much easier to find out of the way places.
replyContent: Hi Greg, Thank you for taking the time to let us know how you like the app. Happy camping!

content: I'm familiar with most campground locator apps and this is one of the best. It's very simple to use and the data is excellent. Location icons are color-coded so you tell at a glance whether the campground is a state park or a Forest Service location, for example. Click on an icon for details. It has search capability and you can build custom lists of favorite spots. You can't go wrong with this one.
Great resource! nicely done!
replyContent: Thanks Spencer, have a good time!

content: Used the related web database for years, but an app is much more convenient when on the go. Totally worth the price. Thanks.
Good number of campsites listed. Very good search. Perfect companion for trip planning and road trips.
So far so good
Great App! Found some cool local spots and helps us plan our adventures in advance!
Planning to drive and camp the US this summer. This app will surely make it a success.
Easy to use and has most public  campsites.

Very good  program...couple things I wish it had...needs a key of the colors (go to help to get the meaning of them)...and a way to add campground that's aren't in the database...would also be nice if it had it's own database for ratings and such.
We've found some fantastic camping with this app. The links to web sites and phone numbers are very helpful.
replyContent: Hi Cathy, So glad to hear you like the app. Happy camping!

content: While statting a 2 month road trip out to the West Coast from the Midwest, I have tried this app and it found me beautiful and free campsites on the Yellowstone River in Montana when I really needed a place to stop over for the night, around midnight.  Absolutely worth it even if it was only for that night, but looking forward to using it more often in the future.
Convenient with lots of good info.  I don't go out without it.  Very useful.
Saved me money and time.
Seems to take a long time if ever to respond and find campgrounds.  Our map would show campgrounds in several areas and the app showed no campgrounds.  Some areas is worked really good.
replyContent: Hello, Could you pick a campground near where  you saw the differences and use the report an issue feature so we can investigate? Kampnik's database is focused on public car accessible campgrounds with 5 or more sites, so that could account for the difference but we want to investigate to be sure.

content: Could not search by state , this is my first time using it hopefully it corrects it self , when I get in out of it at another time ,
replyContent: Hi Keith, To see campgrounds for a state drag your finger on the map to the state you want to view. You can also zoom out or in the map to see more or less campgrounds. To see a list of campgrounds based on distance from the center of the map tap the list button in the toolbar. Hope this helps, happy camping!

content: Most information is accurate.  I Am sure I will continue to use it a lot.
replyContent: Hi Jeff, We are so glad to hear you are enjoying the app. Happy camping!

content: Im on the road most of the time. I dont know what id do if this app didnt find me a place to sleep each nite. The map is a little balky as it tries to load all the camps as u move it around but it is essential to my travels.

It's a nice interface built on a constantly updating database.   It works well offline,  so we were able to locate camp sites throughout our trip.   Great directions to campsites with updating distance (careful,  it includes distance AFTER turnoff from main highway!) Descriptions appear very accurate.

I took my mom camping in her new rv, used this app to find a beautiful campsite. I like how there are links available to pictures, reviews, maps, driving directions for phone gps, etc. With very little effort on my part we navigated easily through an area we were completely unfamiliar with. No stress, and we were very happy with our campsite!
Great app for finding camping spots that are not private campgrounds.
Great app, use it all the time

The app isn't as robust as I hoped it would be. It definitely needs a filter option. I understand you have received feedback to the contrary due to others not turning off the filter when done, however, that's a user education issue and the lack of the feature is a detriment to the app. Additionally the ability to filter by campground type (RV, tent, cabin) is needed as well. E.g. Squirrel Meadows Cabin in the Â Caribou-Targhee National Forest isn't currently listed in the app at all. This app has great potential.
replyContent: Hi Renee, Thank you for taking the time to send us feedback. We are seriously considering the feature. If you are up for it, shoot us an email so that when we have a solid idea of how to do this in a dead simple way we can send you our ideas and get your feedback.

content: Used it to cross Canada!
This app is fantastic for campers travelling across country. Lots of campgrounds in an easy to use app!
Has served us well on our road trip and even works great on airplane mode
We like it and find it easy to use.
replyContent: Hi Wally, Thanks for your review. We're glad to hear you like the app. Happy camping!

content: We love finding new places to camp as we discover America  super easy-to-use and love the links to the campgrounds makes trip planning super easy
replyContent: Hi Doug, We are so glad to hear you like Kampnik. Happy trails!!

content: This is poor for two primary reasons which seem fundamental to me. Can't refine search to narrow out RVs or any other preferences. Is limited in sites it lists throughout BC.
replyContent: Hi Shannon, Adding a feature filter is something we struggled with. We were going to add it, but feedback told us users tend to forget a filter has been turned on and forget to turn it off. This is something we will reevaluate and your feedback is helpful. For BC campgrounds, we are verifying a Canada campground update which should be out soon.

content: Great and accurate at least for CA
replyContent: Hi Ilya, We are so glad to hear you like Kampnik, and want you to know we are working on an update to our CA campground data. Should be out in an update soon.

content: Great

When we moved to Houston we had a hard time finding places to go outdoors, a chance encounter with the developer of this app has changed everything!! Thank you so much!!! Hope you two are enjoying the outdoors as much as we are now! Sonny, Kristy, and Dexter.
replyContent: Hi Chris, It was great to meet the family and we're so glad to hear you are finding places to have fun! Have a great summer!

content: 1 stop shop to plan  your trip,  my 1st app to go to. Wish it was available for ios
replyContent: Hi Don, Thanks for the review, and we're happy you like the app. An iOS version is now available for download.

content: Great for bikers who camp to save a few bucks.
Very easy to use.  Includes ALL car/RV accessible public campgrounds.  Covers all of the US and Canada.  Links up to reservation web sites and phone numbers.  For only $5,  what's not to like?
